<DOC><DOCNO> AP880308-0277 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-08-88 0036EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-OilPrices     03-08 0174</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Oil Prices,0185</SECOND><HEAD>Crude Oil Futures Slide</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Crude oil futures have retreated in response torenewed fears of OPEC price discounting.   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, contracts for Aprildelivery of West Texas Intermediate crude oil settled at $15.37 per42-gallon barrel on Monday, down 22 cents from Friday's close of$15.59.   Among refined products, the April contract for wholesale No. 2heating oil slid 0.13 cent to 43.41 cents. Wholesale unleadedgasoline fell 0.57 cent to 43.94 cents a gallon.   ``I think the catalyst behind today's decline is additionalrumors about OPEC individual nations offering discounts tocustomers,'' said William Byers, an oil analyst with Bear, Stearnsandamp; Co.   Byers said the rumors of price discounting by members of theOrganization of Petroleum Exporting Countries partly grew out ofreports that a delegation from the United Arab Emirates wasvisiting Tokyo this week.   ``The rumors are really all over the map,'' he said.   Reports that OPEC might push for more production controls helpedboost prices on Friday.</TEXT></DOC>